HEADWORD: Scourger
<hw>Scour"ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who scourges or
punishes; one who afflicts severely.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The West must own the <qex>scourger</qex> of the world.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scourse</ent>⟦br⟧
